"According to your needs you can view the whole work area, only the "
"elements included in the current camera shot, or visualize the whole "
"scene in a 3D environment. The viewer can also be frozen, so that the "
"visualization is not updated until you enter with the pointer in the "
"viewer. When the preview mode is activated, the viewer can display the "
"rendered animation as in the final render (see  :ref:`Previewing the "
"Animation <previewing_the_animation>`  )."
