#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:1131
msgid ""
"Inserting or deleting frames can be useful if you want to change the "
"timing of the animation, for instance if you want to slow down or speed "
"up an animation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:1133
msgid ""
"When a frame is inserted, the current frame cells are duplicated, and all"
" the following cells are shifted down (right in the Timeline). If "
"animation keys are defined for object transformations and FX parameters, "
"they will be shifted down (or right in the Timeline) as well, to keep the"
" animation consistency (see  :ref:`Animating Objects <animating_objects>`"
"  and  :ref:`Editing FX Settings <editing_fx_settings>`  )."
