"copied into the related default folders of the current project (see  "
":ref:`Project Default Folders <project_default_folders>`  )."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:1462
msgid ""
"All the files that were located in external folders (i.e. the ones loaded"
" in the scene by using absolute paths), will remain where they are."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:1464
msgid ""
"While the material is automatically imported and saved in the current "
"project, the scene file will not be saved until you will save it by using"
" the Save Scene... or Save Scene As... commands."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:1466
msgid ""
"It is also possible to import one or several scenes into the current "
"project with no need to load and save them by using the Import Scene "
"command."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:1468
msgid ""
"In this case both the material files located in the original project "
"default folders and the scene file will be copied in the related default "
"folders of the current project."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:1470
msgid ""
"If the scene you import contains a file whose name is the same as a file "
"already existing in the destination default folder, you will prompted "
"whether to keep the existing file, overwrite it with the new one, or "
"rename it adding a suffix you can decide. In this way you can control if "
"files you are importing were already imported previously, or manage files"
" that share the same name."
